  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/kindness-charity-and-love,President Thomas S. Monson,4,"My dear brethren, I am honored by the privilege to address you in this worldwide gathering of faithful holders of the priesthood of God. This evening I reference a topic about which I have spoken before."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/kindness-charity-and-love,President Thomas S. Monson,5,"The prophet Mormon outlined one of the key characteristics of the Savior and which is to be emulated by His disciples. Said he:"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/kindness-charity-and-love,President Thomas S. Monson,6,"“And if a man be meek and lowly in heart, and confesses by the power of the Holy Ghost that Jesus is the Christ, he must needs have charity; for if he have not charity he is nothing; wherefore he must needs have charity."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/kindness-charity-and-love,President Thomas S. Monson,7,"“And charity suffereth long, and is kind, and envieth not, and is not puffed up, seeketh not her own, is not easily provoked. …"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/kindness-charity-and-love,President Thomas S. Monson,8,"“Wherefore, my beloved brethren, if ye have not charity, ye are nothing, for charity never faileth. Wherefore, cleave unto charity, which is the greatest of all, for all things must fail—"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/kindness-charity-and-love,President Thomas S. Monson,9,"“But charity is the pure love of Christ, and it endureth forever; and whoso is found possessed of it at the last day, it shall be well with him.”"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/kindness-charity-and-love,President Thomas S. Monson,10,"Brethren, we do not honor the priesthood of God if we are not kind to others."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/kindness-charity-and-love,President Thomas S. Monson,11,"My dear friend and associate Elder Joseph B. Wirthlin was truly a kind man. Said he:"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/kindness-charity-and-love,President Thomas S. Monson,12,"“Kindness is the essence of a celestial life. Kindness is how a Christlike person treats others. Kindness should permeate all of our words and actions at work, at school, at church, and especially in our homes."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/kindness-charity-and-love,President Thomas S. Monson,13,"“Jesus, our Savior, was the epitome of kindness and compassion.”"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/kindness-charity-and-love,President Thomas S. Monson,14,"The scriptures teach us that the righteous exercise of the priesthood is dependent upon our living the principles of kindness, charity, andlove. In the Doctrine and Covenants we read:"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/kindness-charity-and-love,President Thomas S. Monson,15,"“No power or influence can or ought to be maintained by virtue of the priesthood, only by persuasion, … by gentleness and meekness, and by love unfeigned;"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/kindness-charity-and-love,President Thomas S. Monson,16,"“By kindness, and pure knowledge, which shall greatly enlarge the soul without hypocrisy, and without guile.”"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/kindness-charity-and-love,President Thomas S. Monson,17,"Brethren, let us examine our lives and determine to follow the Savior’s example by being kind, loving, and charitable. And as we do so, we will be in a better position to call down the powers of heaven for ourselves, for our families, and for our fellow travelers in this sometimes difficult journey back to our heavenly home. I so pray in the name of Jesus Christ the Lord, amen."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/kindness-charity-and-love,President Thomas S. Monson,18,Notes
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/kindness-charity-and-love,President Thomas S. Monson,19,"Moroni 7:44–47."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/kindness-charity-and-love,President Thomas S. Monson,20,"Joseph B. Wirthlin, “The Virtue of Kindness,”EnsignorLiahona,May 2005, 26."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/kindness-charity-and-love,President Thomas S. Monson,21,"Doctrine and Covenants 121:41–42."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,4,"Brothers and sisters, I, like all of you, recognize we are seeing the hastening of the Lord’s work through President Thomas S. Monson and his message this morning. President Monson, we love you, sustain you, and ever pray for you, “our prophet dear.”"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,5,"We have felt an outpouring of the Spirit this weekend. Whether you are here in this great hall or watching from homes or gathered in meetinghouses in distant parts of the world, you have had the opportunity to feel the Spirit of the Lord. That Spirit confirms to your hearts and minds the truths taught at this conference."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,6,"Consider the words of this familiar hymn:"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,7,Let the Holy Spirit guide;
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,8,Let him teach us what is true.
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,9,"He will testify of Christ,"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,10,Light our minds with heaven’s view.
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,11,"From latter-day revelation we know that the Godhead is comprised of three distinct and separate beings: our Father in Heaven; His Only Begotten Son, Jesus Christ; and the Holy Ghost. We know that “the Father has a body of flesh and bones as tangible as man’s; the Son also; but the Holy Ghost has not a body of flesh and bones, but is a personage of Spirit. Were it not so, the Holy Ghost could not dwell in us.”"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,12,"My message today focuses on the importance of the Holy Ghost in our lives. Our Father in Heaven knew that in mortality we would face challenges, tribulation, and turmoil; He knew we would wrestle with questions, disappointments, temptations, and weaknesses. To give us mortal strength and divine guidance, He provided the Holy Spirit, another name for the Holy Ghost."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,13,"The Holy Ghost binds us to the Lord. By divine assignment, He inspires, testifies, teaches, and prompts us to walk in the light of the Lord. We have the sacred responsibility to learn to recognize His influence in our lives and respond."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,14,"Remember the Lord’s promise: “I will impart unto you of my Spirit, which shall enlighten your mind, which shall fill your soul with joy.”I love that assurance. Joy that fills our souls brings with it an eternal perspective in contrast to day-to-day living. That joy comes as peace amidst hardship or heartache. It provides comfort and courage, unfolds the truths of the gospel, and expands our love for the Lord and all God’s children. Although the need for such blessings is so great, in many ways the world has forgotten and forsaken them."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,15,"Each week as we partake of the holy sacrament, we make a covenant to “always remember him,” the Lord Jesus Christ, and His atoning sacrifice. When we keep this sacred covenant, thepromise is given that we “may always have his Spirit to be with [us].”"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,16,How do we do that?
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,17,"First,we strive to live worthy of the Spirit."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,18,"The Holy Ghost accompanies those who are “strict to remember the Lord their God from day to day.”As the Lord counseled, we must “lay aside the things of this world, and seek for the things of a better,”for “the Spirit of the Lord doth not dwell in unholy temples.”We must always try to obey God’s laws, study the scriptures, pray, attend the temple, and live true to thethirteenth article of faith, “being honest, true, chaste, benevolent, virtuous, and … doing good to all men.”"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,19,"Second,we must be willing to receive the Spirit."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,20,"The Lord has promised, “I will tell you in your mind and in your heart, by the Holy Ghost, which shall come upon you and which shall dwell in your heart.”I began to understand this as a young missionary in Scotch Plains, New Jersey. One hot July morning my companion and I felt prompted to look up a Temple Square referral. We knocked on the door of the Elwood Schaffer home. Mrs. Schaffer politely turned us away."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,21,"As she began to shut the door, I felt to do something I had never done before and have never done since! I stuck my foot in the door, and I asked, “Is there anyone else who might be interested in our message?” Her 16-year-old daughter, Marti, did have an interest and had fervently prayed for guidance just the day before. Marti met with us, and in time her mother participated in the discussions. Both of them joined the Church."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,22,"Resulting from Marti’s baptism, 136 people, including many of her own family, have been baptized and made gospel covenants. How grateful I am that I listened to the Spirit and stuck my foot in the door on that hot July day. Marti and a number of her dear family members are here today."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,23,"Third,we must recognize the Spirit when it comes."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,24,"My experience has been that the Spirit most often communicates as a feeling. You feel it in words that are familiar to you, that make sense to you, that prompt you. Consider the response of the Nephites as they listened to the Lord pray for them: “And the multitude did hear and do bear record; and their hearts were open and they did understand in their hearts the words which he prayed.”They felt in their hearts the words of His prayer. The voice of the Holy Spirit is still and small."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,25,"In the Old Testament, Elijah contended with the priests of Baal. The priests expected the “voice” of Baal to come down as thunder and light their sacrifice with fire. But there was no voice, and there was no fire."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,26,"On a later occasion, Elijah prayed. “And, behold, the Lord passed by, and a great and strong wind rent the mountains, and brake in pieces the rocks before the Lord; but the Lord was not in the wind: and after the wind an earthquake; but the Lord was not in the earthquake:"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,27,"“And after the earthquake a fire; but the Lord was not in the fire: and after the fire a still small voice.”"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,28,Do you know that voice?
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,29,"President Monson has taught, “As we pursue the journey of life, let us learn the language of the Spirit.”The Spirit speaks words that we feel. These feelings are gentle, a nudge to act, to do something, to say something, to respond in a certain way. If we are casual or complacent in our worship, drawn off and desensitized by worldly pursuits, we find ourselves diminished in our ability to feel. Nephi said to Laman and Lemuel, “Ye have heard his voice from time to time; and he hath spoken unto you in a still small voice, but ye were past feeling, that ye could not feel [the] words.”"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,30,"Last June, I was on an assignment to South America. We were on a tight 10-day schedule visiting Colombia, Peru, and Ecuador. An enormous earthquake had killed hundreds, injured tens of thousands, damaged and destroyed homes and communities in the Ecuadorian cities of Portoviejo and Manta. I felt prompted to add to our schedule a visit to members living in those cities. With damage to the roads, we weren’t sure we could get there. In fact, we had been told we could not get there, but the prompting would not go away. Consequently, we were blessed and were able to visit both cities."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,31,"With such short notice, I expected that only a few local priesthood leaders would attend the hastily organized gatherings. However, we arrived at each stake center to find the chapels filled all the way back to the stage. Some who attended were the stalwarts of the region, the pioneers who had held fast to the Church, encouraging others to join them in worship and to feel the Spirit in their lives. Sitting on the front rows were the members who had lost loved ones and neighbors in the earthquake. I felt prompted to bestow an apostolic blessing upon all who were in attendance, one of my very first given. Though I was standing at the front of that room, it was as if my hands were on each of their heads, and I felt the words of the Lord pouring forth."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,32,"It didn’t end there. I felt prompted to speak to them just as Jesus Christ had done when visiting the people in the Americas. “He took their little children … and blessed them, and prayed unto the Father for them.”We were in Ecuador, we were about our Father’s business, and these were His children."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,33,"Fourth,we must act on thefirstprompting."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,34,"Remember the words of Nephi. “I was led by the Spirit, not knowing beforehand the things which I should do. Nevertheless,” he said, “I went forth.”"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,35,"And so must we. We must be confident in our first promptings. Sometimes we rationalize; we wonder if we arefeeling a spiritual impression or if it is just our own thoughts. When we begin to second-guess, even third-guess, our feelings—and we all have—we are dismissing the Spirit; we are questioning divine counsel. The Prophet Joseph Smith taught that if you will listen to the first promptings, you will get it right nine times out of ten."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,36,"Now a caution: don’t expect fireworks because you responded to the Holy Ghost. Remember, you are about the work of the still, small voice."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,37,"While serving as a mission president in New York City, I was with some of our missionaries in a restaurant in the Bronx. A young family came in and sat near us. They appeared golden for the gospel. I watched our missionaries as they continued to visit with me, then noticed as the family concluded their meal and slipped out the door. Then I said, “Elders, there’s a lesson here today. You saw a lovely family come into this restaurant. What should we have done?”"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,38,"One of the elders spoke up quickly: “I thought about getting up and going over to talk to them. I felt the nudge, but I didn’t respond.”"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,39,"“Elders,” I said, “we must always act on our first prompting. That nudge you felt was the Holy Ghost!”"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,40,"First promptings are pure inspiration from heaven. When they confirm or testify to us, we need to recognize them for what they are and never let them slip past. So often, it is the Spirit inspiring us to reach out to someone in need, family and friends in particular. “Thus … the still small voice, which whispereth through and pierceth all things,”points us to opportunities to teach the gospel, to bear testimony of the Restoration and Jesus Christ, to offer support and concern, and to rescue one of God’s precious children."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,41,"Think of it as being what is called a first responder. In most communities the first responders to a tragedy, disaster, or calamity are firefighters, police officers, paramedics. They arrive with lights flashing, and may I add, we are so incredibly grateful for them. The Lord’s way is less obvious but requires just as immediate a response. The Lord knows the needs of all His children—and He knows who is prepared to help. If we let the Lord know in our morning prayers that we are ready, He will call on us to respond. If we respond, He will call on us time and time again and we will find ourselves on what President Monson calls “the Lord’s errand.”We will become spiritual first responders bringing help from on high."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,42,"If we pay attention to the promptings that come to us, we will grow in the spirit of revelation and receive more and more Spirit-driven insight and direction. The Lord has said, “Put your trust in that Spirit which leadeth to do good.”"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,43,"May we take seriously the Lord’s call to “be of good cheer, for I will lead you along.”He leads us by the Holy Ghost. May we live close to the Spirit, acting quickly upon our first promptings, knowing they come from God. I bear witness of the power of the Holy Ghost to guide us, guard us, and ever be with us, in the name of Jesus Christ, amen."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/let-the-holy-spirit-guide,Elder Ronald A. Rasband,44,Notes
