  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/our-good-shepherd,Elder Dale G. Renlund,36,"The novelLes Misérables,by Victor Hugo (1802–85), tells the story of Jean Valjean, who committed a minor crime by stealing a loaf of bread to feed his sister’s family. Sentenced to a term of 5 years’ imprisonment, Valjean spent 19 years doing hard labor because of four failed escape attempts. He emerged from prison a hardened and bitter man."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/our-good-shepherd,Elder Dale G. Renlund,37,"Because of his criminal record, Valjean was unable to find employment, food, and lodging. Exhausted and demoralized, he was finally given lodging with the bishop of Digne, who showed Valjean kindness and compassion. During the night, Valjean surrendered to a sense of hopelessness and stole the bishop’s silverware and ran away."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/our-good-shepherd,Elder Dale G. Renlund,38,"Valjean was captured and returned to the bishop. Inexplicably and contrary to Valjean’s expectations, the bishop told the police that Valjean had been given the silverware and insisted that Valjean take two silver candlesticks as well. (See Hugo,Les Misérables[1987], book 2, chapters 10–12.)"
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/our-good-shepherd,Elder Dale G. Renlund,39,"See Hugo,Les Misérables,book 1, chapter 10."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/our-good-shepherd,Elder Dale G. Renlund,40,"The narrator asks,Toutefois, la gale de la brebis doit-elle faire reculer le pasteur?(Hugo,Les Misérables[1985], book 1, chapter 10, page 67).Gale,in veterinary pathology, refers to any of a variety of skin diseases caused by parasitic mites and characterized by loss of hair and scabby eruptions (“mange” in English). This phrase has been translated in various ways into English."
  2017,"04",/general-conference/2017/04/our-good-shepherd,Elder Dale G. Renlund,41,The narrator’s humorous editorial comment about the conventionist isMais quelle brebis!It has occasionally been translated as “But what a black sheep.”
